The paper discusses a new automated framework of grille cipher that can satisfy both content and channel security simultaneously. This topic falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The proposed method uses semantic image inpainting, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the difference and connection between cryptography and steganography, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
